@graph.rdfs:comment: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroomâ€™s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.
@graph.rdfs:label: correctionsPolicy

@graph.rdfs:comment: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical) [[branch]].
@graph.rdfs:label: branchOf

@graph.rdfs:comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: aggregateRating

@graph.rdfs:comment: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].
@graph.rdfs:label: image

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoIntersects

@graph.rdfs:comment: URL of the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: url

@graph.rdfs:comment: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.
@graph.rdfs:label: LodgingBusiness

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.
@graph.rdfs:label: potentialAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: Awards won by or for this item.
@graph.rdfs:label: awards

@graph.rdfs:comment:
A hotel is an establishment that provides lodging paid on a short-term basis (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.
@graph.rdfs:label: Hotel

@graph.rdfs:comment: The geo coordinates of the place.
@graph.rdfs:label: geo

@graph.rdfs:comment: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.
@graph.rdfs:label: Organization

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoEquals

@graph.rdfs:comment: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.
@graph.rdfs:label: naics

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoCovers

@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.
@graph.rdfs:label: disambiguatingDescription

@graph.rdfs:comment: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.
@graph.rdfs:label: location

@graph.rdfs:comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.
@graph.rdfs:label: areaServed

@graph.rdfs:comment: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.
@graph.rdfs:label: parentOrganization

@graph.rdfs:comment: Review of the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: reviews

@graph.rdfs:comment: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.
@graph.rdfs:label: sameAs

@graph.rdfs:comment: The longitude of a location. For example ```-122.08585``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).
@graph.rdfs:label: longitude

@graph.rdfs:comment: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.
@graph.rdfs:label: brand

@graph.rdfs:comment: The geographic area where the service is provided.
@graph.rdfs:label: serviceArea

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoWithin

@graph.rdfs:comment: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.
@graph.rdfs:label: vatID

@graph.rdfs:comment: A review of the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: review

@graph.rdfs:comment: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.
@graph.rdfs:label: makesOffer

@graph.rdfs:comment: The name of the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: name

@graph.rdfs:comment: An award won by or for this item.
@graph.rdfs:label: award

@graph.rdfs:comment: The opening hours of a certain place.
@graph.rdfs:label: openingHoursSpecification

@graph.rdfs:comment: The date that this organization was dissolved.
@graph.rdfs:label: dissolutionDate

@graph.rdfs:comment: An associated logo.
@graph.rdfs:label: logo

@graph.rdfs:comment: A URL to a map of the place.
@graph.rdfs:label: map

@graph.rdfs:comment: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.
@graph.rdfs:label: member

@graph.rdfs:comment: The price range of the business, for example ```$$$```.
@graph.rdfs:label: priceRange

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoCrosses

@graph.rdfs:comment: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).
@graph.rdfs:label: seeks

@graph.rdfs:comment: People working for this organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: employees

@graph.rdfs:comment: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.
@graph.rdfs:label: subjectOf

@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of employees in an organization, e.g. business.
@graph.rdfs:label: numberOfEmployees

@graph.rdfs:comment: A person who founded this organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: founder

@graph.rdfs:comment: A slogan or motto associated with the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: slogan

@graph.rdfs:comment: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.
@graph.rdfs:label: memberOf

@graph.rdfs:comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.
@graph.rdfs:label: Place

@graph.rdfs:comment: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.
@graph.rdfs:label: paymentAccepted

@graph.rdfs:comment: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.
@graph.rdfs:label: ownershipFundingInfo

@graph.rdfs:comment: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors.  If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value
@graph.rdfs:label: publicAccess

@graph.rdfs:comment: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).
@graph.rdfs:label: latitude

@graph.rdfs:comment: nonprofitStatus indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.
@graph.rdfs:label: nonprofitStatus

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: "they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)
@graph.rdfs:label: geoTouches

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether some facility (e.g. [[FoodEstablishment]], [[CovidTestingFacility]]) offers a service that can be used by driving through in a car. In the case of [[CovidTestingFacility]] such facilities could potentially help with social distancing from other potentially-infected users.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasDriveThroughService

@graph.rdfs:comment: The currency accepted.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".
@graph.rdfs:label: currenciesAccepted

@graph.rdfs:comment: An alias for the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: alternateName

@graph.rdfs:comment: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.
@graph.rdfs:label: maximumAttendeeCapacity

@graph.rdfs:comment: A person who founded this organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: founders

@graph.rdfs:comment: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.
@graph.rdfs:label: unnamedSourcesPolicy

@graph.rdfs:comment: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.
@graph.rdfs:label: department

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoCoveredBy

@graph.rdfs:comment:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual, e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a [[funder]]) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.
@graph.rdfs:label: publishingPrinciples

@graph.rdfs:comment: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.
@graph.rdfs:label: checkinTime

@graph.rdfs:comment: A description of the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: description

@graph.rdfs:comment: Email address.
@graph.rdfs:label: email

@graph.rdfs:comment: The telephone number.
@graph.rdfs:label: telephone

@graph.rdfs:comment: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.
@graph.rdfs:label: subOrganization

@graph.rdfs:comment: The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'. * Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```. * Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00```. * Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>. * If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.
@graph.rdfs:label: openingHours

@graph.rdfs:comment: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.
@graph.rdfs:label: amenityFeature

@graph.rdfs:comment: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.
@graph.rdfs:label: taxID

@graph.rdfs:comment: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).
@graph.rdfs:label: knowsLanguage

@graph.rdfs:comment: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].
@graph.rdfs:label: specialOpeningHoursSpecification

@graph.rdfs:comment: The place where the Organization was founded.
@graph.rdfs:label: foundingLocation

@graph.rdfs:comment: A URL to a map of the place.
@graph.rdfs:label: maps

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: "they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)
@graph.rdfs:label: geoDisjoint

@graph.rdfs:comment: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.
@graph.rdfs:label: checkoutTime

@graph.rdfs:comment: A contact point for a person or organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: contactPoints

@graph.rdfs:comment: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.
@graph.rdfs:label: isAccessibleForFree

@graph.rdfs:comment: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.\n\nFor example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.
@graph.rdfs:label: branchCode

@graph.rdfs:comment: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.
@graph.rdfs:label: funder

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasOfferCatalog

@graph.rdfs:comment: A URL to a map of the place.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasMap

@graph.rdfs:comment: The most generic type of item.
@graph.rdfs:label: Thing

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoOverlaps

@graph.rdfs:comment: Photographs of this place.
@graph.rdfs:label: photos

@graph.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.
@graph.rdfs:label: containedInPlace

@graph.rdfs:comment: An organization identifier as defined in ISO 6523(-1). Note that many existing organization identifiers such as [leiCode](https://schema.org/leiCode), [duns](https://schema.org/duns) and [vatID](https://schema.org/vatID) can be expressed as an ISO 6523 identifier by setting the ICD part of the ISO 6523 identifier accordingly.
@graph.rdfs:label: iso6523Code

@graph.rdfs:comment: Keywords or tags used to describe some item. Multiple textual entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas, or by repeating the property.
@graph.rdfs:label: keywords

@graph.rdfs:comment:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.
@graph.rdfs:label: numberOfRooms

@graph.rdfs:comment: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.
@graph.rdfs:label: diversityStaffingReport

@graph.rdfs:comment: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.
@graph.rdfs:label: knowsAbout

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates a ProductReturnPolicy that may be applicable.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasProductReturnPolicy

@graph.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.
@graph.rdfs:label: containsPlace

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#mainEntityBackground) for details.
@graph.rdfs:label: mainEntityOfPage

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.
@graph.rdfs:label: smokingAllowed

@graph.rdfs:comment: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).
@graph.rdfs:label: starRating

@graph.rdfs:comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.
@graph.rdfs:label: additionalType

@graph.rdfs:comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.
@graph.rdfs:label: isicV4

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoContains

@graph.rdfs:comment: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.
@graph.rdfs:label: containedIn

@graph.rdfs:comment: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.
@graph.rdfs:label: legalName

@graph.rdfs:comment: The fax number.
@graph.rdfs:label: faxNumber

@graph.rdfs:comment: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsroomâ€™s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.
@graph.rdfs:label: diversityPolicy

@graph.rdfs:comment: Someone working for this organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: employee

@graph.rdfs:comment: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.
@graph.rdfs:label: sponsor

@graph.rdfs:comment: The date that this organization was founded.
@graph.rdfs:label: foundingDate

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.
@graph.rdfs:label: petsAllowed

@graph.rdfs:comment: A contact point for a person or organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: contactPoint

@graph.rdfs:comment: A member of this organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: members

@graph.rdfs:comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.
@graph.rdfs:label: event

@graph.rdfs:comment: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.
@graph.rdfs:label: LocalBusiness

@graph.rdfs:comment: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].
@graph.rdfs:label: funding

@graph.rdfs:comment: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.
@graph.rdfs:label: tourBookingPage

@graph.rdfs:comment: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.
@graph.rdfs:label: duns

@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.
@graph.rdfs:label: interactionStatistic

@graph.rdfs:comment: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroomâ€™s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.
@graph.rdfs:label: actionableFeedbackPolicy

@graph.rdfs:comment: A photograph of this place.
@graph.rdfs:label: photo

@graph.rdfs:comment: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of [[Thing]], such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#identifierBg) for more details.
@graph.rdfs:label: identifier

@graph.rdfs:comment: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. https://schema.org/width, https://schema.org/color, https://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.
@graph.rdfs:label: additionalProperty

@graph.rdfs:comment: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.
@graph.rdfs:label: audience

@graph.rdfs:comment: Alumni of an organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: alumni

@graph.rdfs:comment: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: events

@graph.rdfs:comment: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].
@graph.rdfs:label: availableLanguage

@graph.rdfs:comment: Products owned by the organization or person.
@graph.rdfs:label: owns

@graph.rdfs:comment: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasCredential

@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasMerchantReturnPolicy

@graph.rdfs:comment: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.
@graph.rdfs:label: ethicsPolicy

@graph.rdfs:comment: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.
@graph.rdfs:label: leiCode

@graph.rdfs:comment: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasPOS

@graph.rdfs:comment: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.
@graph.rdfs:label: globalLocationNumber

@graph.rdfs:comment: Physical address of the item.
@graph.rdfs:label: address
